A light aircraft made an emergency landing in  the middle of the road near Stellenbosch on Wednesday. ER24 said one of the plane's occupants sustained serious injuries while the other escaped with minor injuries. The men were found seated near the downed aircraft on the R44 between Stellenbosch and Strand, the paramedic service said. They were transported to Mediclinic Stellenbosch. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to theÂ Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.